1. Synchronous code on a single thread:
```java
public class SynchronousExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Synchronous code on a single thread starting...");

        // Synchronous task
        for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
            System.out.println("Synchronous task " + i);
        }

        System.out.println("Synchronous code on a single thread ending...");
    }
}
```

2. Asynchronous code on a single thread using CompletableFuture:
```java
import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;

public class AsynchronousExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Asynchronous code on a single thread starting...");

        // Asynchronous task
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
                System.out.println("Asynchronous task " + i);
            }
        }).join();

        System.out.println("Asynchronous code on a single thread ending...");
    }
}
```

3. Multithreading code using Java threads:
```java
public class MultithreadingExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Multithreading code starting...");

        // Multithreading task
        Thread thread1 = new Thread(() -> {
            for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
                System.out.println("Multithreading task A" + i);
            }
        });

        Thread thread2 = new Thread(() -> {
            for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
                System.out.println("Multithreading task B" + i);
            }
        });

        thread1.start();
        thread2.start();

        // Ensuring main thread waits for both threads to finish
        try {
            thread1.join();
            thread2.join();
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }

        System.out.println("Multithreading code ending...");
    }
}
```

These examples demonstrate synchronous and asynchronous code running on a single thread and multithread in Java.

